Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian) Middle Wild Goat II pottery oinochoe; exterior: cream slip, dark brown paint; hindquarters of a fallow deer to left, brown band below; filling ornaments: lozenge, quatrefoil pattern with spikes.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.601)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 93, Nau 36, pl. 8h)
